{"word":"Ἑκάλειος","slug":"Ἑκάλειος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n31580\" key=\"*(eka/leios\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ἑκάλειος Ζεύς</orth> <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">[ᾰ]</pron>, from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἑκάλη,</foreign> a lady who entertained Theseus, and for this received at Athens the yearly honour of the <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ἑκαλήσια</orth> [<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἱερά</foreign>]: hence the epith. was given to Zeus as worshipped on the same day, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0007.tlg001:14\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Plu.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Thes.\">Thes.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14</biblScope></bibl>.</entryFree>"}]}